This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, the paper deals with topics such as data compression, string algorithms, and data structures for efficient access and manipulation of compressed data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques for van Emde Boas style decomposition and longest common extensions queries, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
